d_by":0,"blocking":0,"total_blocking":0},"body":"### Problem\n\n`syntax/qf.vim` has a special case to conceal file path and line number in table of contents lists, but this is not working in 0.11.1 (it was working in 0.10.4).\n\nI believe the regression was caused by #32971 because the new `quickfix_title` doesn't match the regex in qf.vim anymore.\n\nI changed the test in qf.vim to:\n\n```vim\nif has_key(w:, 'qf_toc') || get(w:, 'quickfix_title') =~# '\\<TOC$' || get(w:, 'quickfix_title') == 'Table of contents'\n```\n\nand that fixes the issue but I'm not sure that is the proper fix.\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n- open any help page, for example `:help syntax`\n- press `gO`\n\nI verified this is still the case with `nvim --clean`, no other setup is necessary.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe file paths and line numbers should be concealed to avoid pushing the headings out of the right margin of the window.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\n0.11.1\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nthe feature in vim is implemented differently\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nmacOS 15\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nghostty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-ghostly\n\n### Installation\n\nhomebrew","closed_by":{"login":"justinmk","id":1359421,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjEzNTk0MjE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/1359421?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk","html_url":"https://github.com/justinmk","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/justinmk/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/just